Titulo: Enhanced Ionic Conductivity and Durability of Novel Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Constructing a Heterojunction Based on Transition and Rare Earth Metal Co-doped Ceria

Sentencas: In this work, we develop a novel solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) by constructing a heterostructure electrolyte based on Gd0.15Ni0.05Ce0.8O2-delta (GNDC) and SnO2, which acquires an open circuit voltage of 1.026 V and a maximum power density (MPD) of 879.4 mW cm(-2) at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Enhanced Ionic Conductivity and Durability of Novel Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Constructing a Heterojunction Based on Transition and Rare Earth Metal Co-doped Ceria

Sentencas: It is demonstrated that the composites are a hybrid ionic and protonic conductor with competent conductivity of 0.124-0.220 S cm(-1) at 450-550 degrees C. Further characterization authenticates the valence state alteration of Ni, creating more oxygen vacancies during the tests.
Titulo: Enhanced Ionic Conductivity and Durability of Novel Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Constructing a Heterojunction Based on Transition and Rare Earth Metal Co-doped Ceria
